    <text type="letter"> 
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.02515_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">26 Nelson <hi rend="underline">Square</hi><ptr target="loc.04645_n1"/></name>
                    <name type="place">Bolton.</name>
                    <name type="place">England.</name>
                    <date when="1892-02-24"><hi rend="underline">Feb 24th 1892</hi></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mr Whitman,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Your friend Dr J <choice><sic>Johnson</sic><corr>Johnston</corr></choice><ptr target="n4102"/> 
                of this town has today kindly shown me your letter <choice><sic>recieved</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> by him 
                last week.<ptr target="loc.04645_n2"/> As a young Newspaper Editor, &#38; as one who values your writings
                <hi rend="underline">more</hi> than I can ever attempt to express, please 
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.02516_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                allow me to express my kindest &#38; tenderest sympathies with you in your hours
                of weakness &#38; suffering. Your teachings rest always in my mind like gleams of
                sunlight upon the pathway of the future, &#38; I may say that I never write a leading
                article without trying, as much as lies within me, to hold your 
                <hi rend="underline">"Democratic Vistas"</hi><ptr target="n4122"/> in my mind's eye.</p>
            <p>In conclusion let me subscribe myself</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours ever gratefully</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">Max A Wright.</hi></signed> 
            </closer>
